{"TopicId":220534,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"(Suggestion) Improvement of color palette and surface detail function","CreatedByName":"ohka","CreatedById":226211,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-31T19:31:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ohka","CreatedById":226211,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-31T19:31:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2\u0027s color system is very useful for building ISAS rockets. However, some improvements are possible. First of all, when I want to separate the colors of the rocket and payload, or when I want to paint the battery in monochrome, I think, \u0060\u0060I wish I could save more colors.\u0027\u0027 I think it would be nice to have a palette. To save colors. Color used. You can\u0027t paint a complex rocket in just two space agency theme colors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new feature I would like to propose is the \u0022Surface Detail Function.\u0022 Rocket surfaces vary. Default plastic toy-like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E motor case. We sprayed insulation on Shuttle ET. Ariane 5 looks like a brick. Metal Starship and satellite MLI. I would like to be able to select these details individually for each part. (I\u0027m sure many people would like to recreate the orange color of the shuttle even if it uses methane fuel.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease let me know your opinions as well\uFF01\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-31T19:46:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would love a palette!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-31T23:11:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335597\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698780692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226211\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ohka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, ohka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst of all, when I want to separate the colors of the rocket and payload, or when I want to paint the battery in monochrome,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guy, you know you can\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XfKEpyI.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.20\u0022 height=\u0022676\u0022 width=\u0022963\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XfKEpyI.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-31T23:57:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698793906\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guy, you know you can\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they mean (and I would like) to save that, plus a dozen other ones, and apply them easily to various parts around the craft without having to go back and re-set the colors each time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-31T23:57:36Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2023 11:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 31\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T00:33:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698796640\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they mean (and I would like) to save that, plus a dozen other ones, and apply them easily to various parts around the craft without having to go back and re-set the colors each time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a mod for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022161422\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2913062993\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/214821-color-presets/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:200px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add to this, what I\u0027d like to see is the ability to input RGB and opacity values instead of trying to use sliders to get the right color.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T00:39:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335703\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698798806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a mod for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOooh thank you, I\u0027m not in the \u0022look for a mod\u0022 mindset yet for KSP2 as it\u0027s still new to me, though I already run the game through \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335703\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698798806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add to this, what I\u0027d like to see is the ability to input RGB and opacity values instead of trying to use sliders to get the right color.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I\u0027d love to have all the common ways to pick color. In particular, yesterday I wanted the picker tool. I\u0027d love to be able to say \u0022the color in this area of this part, that\u0027s what I want.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-01T00:39:34Z\u0022 title=\u002211/01/2023 12:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 1\u0022\u003ENovember 1, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T00:46:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, being able to freehand with a paintbrush would be nice.\u00A0 Way outside the scope of the game, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T01:23:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335712\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698799591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, being able to freehand with a paintbrush would be nice.\u00A0 Way outside the scope of the game, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo sorry I don\u0027t mean drawing. I mean the color picker tool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNormally in paint programs, you can use it to pick the color of any pixel on the screen and it\u0027d make the brush that color.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn this case, I\u0027d like to be able to use it to click a part and the game to look at that part, at the section where I clicked it, and figure out what color paint is there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I click on a part I made orange a while ago, my color gets set to orange. I click some yellow paint on a texture of another part, it turns yellow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T07:43:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes to all of this stuff!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSave color swatches into a palette\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDefine colors as RGB values rather than with the slider\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEyedropper for picking a color\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEasier way to switch between apply to part/apply to craft\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-02T14:59:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think a palette is an excellent\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698801837\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/1/2023 at 1:23 AM, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo sorry I don\u0027t mean drawing. I mean the color picker tool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a vague - possibly false - memory of this being mentioned as a planned feature some time ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust being able to \u0022pick\u0022 a colour you\u0027d already used from a craft to reuse it would go a long way towards achieving the functionality of a palette.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335703\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698798806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/1/2023 at 12:33 AM, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a mod for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to stay away from mods in these bug-ridden times...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-02T15:42:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224336211\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698937144\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210559\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NaughtyMonster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, NaughtyMonster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to stay away from mods in these bug-ridden times...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t blame you.\u00A0 I\u0027m simply pointing out that there is a mod that does what you are (kind of) asking about.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-02T15:43:18Z\u0022 title=\u002211/02/2023 03:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 2\u0022\u003ENovember 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Scarecrow71\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}